{"body": "> The problem is that there are heaps of non thread safe usage of Hashes in Rails and the surrounding gems. This needs to be fixed. Instead of littering the whole code base with the synchronize {} blocks, it is better done by creating a fully thread-safe hash-like data structure.\r\n\r\n:+1: :+1: :+1:\r\n\r\n/cc @tenderlove ", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/11336669", "created_at": "2012-12-13T14:44:38Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/8510#issuecomment-11336669", "updated_at": "2012-12-13T14:44:38Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 8510, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/steveklabnik", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/233c279c012ebac792aaa805f966cbc7?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F0c22d45f31acf0f4192c8c12b7a55dee.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/received_events", "gravatar_id": "233c279c012ebac792aaa805f966cbc7", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "steveklabnik", "type": "User", "id": 27786, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/steveklabnik/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237f290bd3543c15100a633"}, "id": 11336669, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/8510"}
